      <h2 id="considerate-condolences-for-colleagues">Considerate Condolences for Colleagues</h2>
      <p></p>
<p>These messages maintain professionalism while offering sincere support.  Keep them concise yet heartfelt, and avoid overly familiar language.</p>
<li>Please accept my sincere condolences on the loss of your [loved one's relationship].</li>
<li>I was saddened to hear of your loss.  My thoughts are with you and your family.</li>
<li> My deepest sympathies to you and your family during this difficult time.</li>
<li> Please know that I am thinking of you during this challenging period.</li>
<li> I offer my heartfelt condolences on your loss.</li>
<li> May [loved one's name] rest in peace.</li>
<li> Please accept my deepest sympathy for your loss.</li>
<li> Thinking of you at this time.  Please reach out if you need anything at work.</li>
<li> I offer my support to you during this difficult period.</li>
<li> Please accept my condolences on your loss.</li>
